1 Writer / Director John Hughes covered all bases ( as usual ) with this bitter - sweet " Sunday Afternoon " family movie . " Curly Sue " is a sweet , precocious orphan , cared for from infancy by " Bill " . The pair live off their wits as they travel the great US of A. Fate matches them with a " very pretty " yuppie lawyer , and the rest is predictable.<br /><br />Kids will love this film , as they can relate to the heroine , played by 9 year old Alisan Poter ( who went on to be the " you go girl ! " of Pepsi commercials ) . The character is supposed to be about 6 or 7 , as she is urged to think about going to school . Some of her vocabulary suggests that she is every day of 9 or older.<br /><br />Similar to " Home Alone " , there is plenty of slap - stick and little fists punching big fat chins . Again , this is " formula " film making , aimed at a young audience . Entertaining and heartwarming . Do n't look for any surprises , but be prepared to shed a tear or two .
