1 Long before " Brokeback Mountain " ( about 23 years before ) , " Deathtrap " was the first time I ever saw two men passionately kissing on screen , and frankly , I was shocked . I understood it in terms of the plot , and it did n't really upset my sensibilities ( not much ) , but it was the first time I ever saw it , at least , in a " mainstream " movie . I thought it was a gutsy move for its time , and took courage for them to try it , especially Christopher Reeve , in the midst of his time as PG - rated Superman . Male bisexuality on screen may have hit its stride with " Brokeback , " but it 's interesting to note this much - earlier incarnation .
